  "title": "HR EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<ul><li>Manage the recruitment and selection process</li><li>Manage employee records, employment agreements, and HR guidelines.</li><li>Administer payroll, manage employee benefits, and handle other HR-related duties.</li><li>Handle the application and renewal of company certifications such as BCA, ISO, GGBS, and others.</li><li>Supervise day-to-day office operations, including purchasing, facility upkeep, and IT coordination.</li><li>Facilitate effective internal communication to ensure seamless business processes across departments.</li><li>Diploma in Human Resources, Business Administraton or a related discipline.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of hands-on experience in HR and administrative functions within the construction sector.</li><li>Solid understanding of human resources principles, employment laws, and regulatory standards.</li><li>Strong verbal and written commnication skills, with the ability to collaborate acrsss all levels of the\norganization.</li><li>Skilled with MS office applications and HR software, including payroll systems.</li><li>Knowedgeable in budgeting, office infrastructure and facility oversight.</li></ul>",
